editorialNotes.tagline: Track and share runs and rides
editorialNotes.standard: Friendly competition with a like-minded sporting community is a big part of Strava's appeal. More than just a GPS, Strava shares your rides and runs automatically, so it's really low maintenance. See your rank on your favourite segment, join distance challenges, and follow your friends, pros and even foes. As they say, "If it’s not on Strava, it didn’t happen".
editorialNotes.short: Fitness challenges to push your training further.

editorialNotes.standard: With detailed plans (including nutrition and cross-training advice), Runna makes an excellent, pocket-size running coach. Lean on the app’s coaches and AI-powered features to help you find your stride, connect with fellow runners, and smash your race-day goals.

An invaluable tool for reaching your weight-loss goals, Lose It! tracks your meals, exercise, and nutrition. Documenting food is effortless with its built-in barcode scanner, searchable list of common grocery items, and database of popular restaurant meals’ nutritional facts. Plus, when you need some extra motivation, the app’s social features make it easy to find inspiration from friends and cheer each other on.
editorialNotes.short: Stay on track and monitor your daily calorie budget.
